There are backchannels, secret informants through the entire system, the entire thing is controlled from the top like the cartels in Mexico. Criminal black markets for drugs and weapons are tightly regulated by the state. So actual free markets must be something else.

Why I like this post so much is the first thing someone would think about when he reads about "natural free markets" are for example drugs on the black market. But that is not true. If you have read Orwell you will know all such black markets are secretly controlled by the state.

Female soldiers in combat roles is one of those lunatic 20th century ideas that seems bizarre to basically anyone today and could make sense only as an obsession in the mentally ill brainwashed religious extremist mind of some Fabian trade unionist freemason in the 1930s.

It's the same sort of logic as "gender equality" as a concept or the legal fiction of homosexual male-to-male "marriage" where the ideologue inherently sees people as depersonalized and interchangeable individual units lacking a real self. It negates the human personality.
You will know real change has come once homosexual marriage is abolished.

At the start of the 20th century Britain was effectively a caste society. A lot of this is simply forgotten today and people just see people having "servants" in old films as an eccentric quirk, but it was a really brutal society. Dmitry Galkovsky has quite good articles on this.

H.G. Wells' story about The Time Machine and Morlocks is not just metaphor for class warfare, in Britain in the time of his childhood there were actual biological differences between people of diff classes, language was so diverse the poor sounded mentally ill to upper classes.
